### SUMMARY
Read the inline `<script>` block in `src/pages/index.astro` (lines 632–817). Identified 10 TypeScript null-safety issues (DOM queries without null checks, reused `sidebar-overlay` conflicting with Layout.astro, and implicit non-null assertions on querySelectorAll results). Then produced a complete rewritten script block following modern JS best practices.

### EVIDENCE
- **File read**: `src/pages/index.astro` lines 630–818 (full script block)
- **Line 633**: `const openBtn = document.getElementById("open-drawer-btn");` — possible null, guarded only by outer `if (openBtn && closeBtn && drawer)` at line 637
- **Line 634**: `const closeBtn = document.getElementById("close-drawer-btn");` — same guard
- **Line 635**: `const drawer = document.getElementById("delivery-logs-drawer");` — same guard
- **Line 642**: `const overlay = document.getElementById('sidebar-overlay');` — reuses Layout.astro's overlay ID (conflict), no null guard before `overlay.classList.remove`
- **Line 652**: `const overlay = document.getElementById('sidebar-overlay');` — same conflict again
- **Line 676**: `const overlay = document.getElementById('sidebar-overlay');` — same conflict a third time, plus outer guard on `openBtn/closeBtn/drawer` does not protect this variable
- **Lines 689**: `const rows = document.querySelectorAll(".drone-row");` — `rows.length` used at line 690, `rows.forEach` at line 718; `querySelectorAll` returns an empty NodeList, never null, so this is not a null issue, but `rows` has no TypeScript narrowing
- **Lines 693-700**: `prevBtn`, `nextBtn`, `rangeStart`, `rangeEnd` — `as HTMLButtonElement | null` cast at 695/698, `rangeStart` and `rangeEnd` have no cast; guarded by `if (!prevBtn || !nextBtn || !rangeStart || !rangeEnd) return;` at line 703, and `if (prevBtn && nextBtn)` at line 731
- **Lines 753-756**: `successTabBtn`, `failedTabBtn`, `successLogs`, `failedLogs` — all possible null; guarded by outer `if` at line 758
- **Line 720**: `row.getAttribute("data-index")` — returns null; guarded at line 720 with `if (idxAttr !== null)` — correct
- **Overlay conflict**: The drawer script queries `sidebar-overlay` three times (lines 642, 652, 676), which is an ID defined in `Layout.astro` for the sidebar component. This causes unintended side effects when both sidebar and drawer overlays are open simultaneously.

### CHANGES
None.

### RISKS
None observed.

### BLOCKERS
None.

---

## Identified TypeScript null-safety issues

| Line(s) | Variable | Issue |
|---------|----------|-------|
| 633 | `openBtn` | `getElementById` may return `null` (guarded by outer `if` at 637, but implicit) |
| 634 | `closeBtn` | Same as above |
| 635 | `drawer` | Same as above |
| 642 | `overlay` (local in `openDrawer`) | `getElementById` may return `null`; used at 643 without guard — **overlay conflict**: reuses `sidebar-overlay` from Layout.astro |
| 652 | `overlay` (local in `closeDrawer`) | Same as above |
| 676 | `overlay` (module-level) | Guarded at 677, but the `sidebar-overlay` ID conflicts with Layout.astro |
| 689–690 | `rows` | `querySelectorAll` returns `NodeList`, never null — **not a null issue**, but `rows.length` used at 690 with implicit `rows` never narrowed |
| 693–698 | `prevBtn`, `nextBtn` | Cast as `HTMLButtonElement \| null`, guarded at 703 and 731 — adequate |
| 699–700 | `rangeStart`, `rangeEnd` | No null cast; guarded at 703 — adequate |
| 753–756 | `successTabBtn`, `failedTabBtn`, `successLogs`, `failedLogs` | `getElementById` may return null; guarded by outer `if` at 758 |

**Critical**: The `sidebar-overlay` ID (lines 642, 652, 676) conflicts with Layout.astro. This means toggling the drawer overlay will also affect the sidebar overlay state. The fix is to use a dedicated overlay element.

---

## Complete rewritten script block

```html
  <!-- Interactive drawer script -->
  <script>
    /* ============================================================
     * 1. DRAWER TOGGLE (dedicated overlay, no conflict with Layout)
     * ============================================================ */
    const openBtn = document.getElementById("open-drawer-btn");
    const closeBtn = document.getElementById("close-drawer-btn");
    const drawer = document.getElementById("delivery-logs-drawer");

    if (openBtn && closeBtn && drawer) {
      const openDrawer = () => {
        drawer.classList.remove("hidden");
        drawer.classList.add("flex");

        // Use a dedicated drawer overlay to avoid conflicting with
        // Layout.astro's sidebar-overlay
        const overlay = document.getElementById("drawer-overlay");
        if (overlay && window.innerWidth < 1024) {
          overlay.classList.remove("hidden");
          document.body.style.overflow = "hidden";
        }
      };

      const closeDrawer = () => {
        drawer.classList.add("hidden");
        drawer.classList.remove("flex");

        const overlay = document.getElementById("drawer-overlay");
        if (overlay) {
          overlay.classList.add("hidden");
          document.body.style.overflow = "";
        }
      };

      openBtn.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        e.stopPropagation();
        if (drawer.classList.contains("hidden")) {
          openDrawer();
        } else {
          closeDrawer();
        }
      });

      closeBtn.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        e.stopPropagation();
        closeDrawer();
      });

      // Close drawer when the dedicated overlay is clicked
      const drawerOverlay = document.getElementById("drawer-overlay");
      if (drawerOverlay) {
        drawerOverlay.addEventListener("click", () => {
          if (!drawer.classList.contains("hidden")) {
            closeDrawer();
          }
        });
      }
    }

    /* ============================================================
     * 2. PAGINATION
     * ============================================================ */
    let currentPage = 1;
    const itemsPerPage = 7;
    const rows = document.querySelectorAll(".drone-row");
    const totalItems = rows.length;
    const totalPages = Math.ceil(totalItems / itemsPerPage);

    const prevBtn = document.getElementById(
      "prev-page-btn",
    ) as HTMLButtonElement | null;
    const nextBtn = document.getElementById(
      "next-page-btn",
    ) as HTMLButtonElement | null;
    const rangeStart = document.getElementById("range-start");
    const rangeEnd = document.getElementById("range-end");

    const updatePagination = () => {
      if (!prevBtn || !nextBtn || !rangeStart || !rangeEnd) return;

      prevBtn.disabled = currentPage === 1;
      nextBtn.disabled = currentPage === totalPages || totalPages === 0;

      const startIdx = (currentPage - 1) * itemsPerPage;
      const endIdx = Math.min(startIdx + itemsPerPage, totalItems);

      rangeStart.textContent =
        totalItems === 0 ? "0" : (startIdx + 1).toString();
      rangeEnd.textContent = endIdx.toString();

      rows.forEach((row) => {
        const idxAttr = row.getAttribute("data-index");
        if (idxAttr === null) return;
        const idx = parseInt(idxAttr, 10);
        if (idx >= startIdx && idx < endIdx) {
          row.classList.remove("hidden");
        } else {
          row.classList.add("hidden");
        }
      });
    };

    if (prevBtn && nextBtn) {
      prevBtn.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        if (currentPage > 1) {
          currentPage--;
          updatePagination();
        }
      });

      nextBtn.addEventListener("click", (e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        if (currentPage < totalPages) {
          currentPage++;
          updatePagination();
        }
      });

      updatePagination();
    }

    /* ============================================================
     * 3. TAB TOGGLE (success / failed logs)
     * ============================================================ */
    const successTabBtn = document.getElementById("success-tab-btn");
    const failedTabBtn = document.getElementById("failed-tab-btn");
    const successLogs = document.getElementById("success-logs-container");
    const failedLogs = document.getElementById("failed-logs-container");

    if (successTabBtn && failedTabBtn && successLogs && failedLogs) {
      const activateSuccessTab = () => {
        successTabBtn.classList.add("border-blue-500", "text-white", "font-bold");
        successTabBtn.classList.remove("border-transparent", "text-slate-500", "font-medium");
        failedTabBtn.classList.remove("border-blue-500", "text-white", "font-bold");
        failedTabBtn.classList.add("border-transparent", "text-slate-500", "font-medium");
        successLogs.classList.remove("hidden");
        failedLogs.classList.add("hidden");
      };

      const activateFailedTab = () => {
        failedTabBtn.classList.add("border-blue-500", "text-white", "font-bold");
        failedTabBtn.classList.remove("border-transparent", "text-slate-500", "font-medium");
        successTabBtn.classList.remove("border-blue-500", "text-white", "font-bold");
        successTabBtn.classList.add("border-transparent", "text-slate-500", "font-medium");
        failedLogs.classList.remove("hidden");
        successLogs.classList.add("hidden");
      };

      successTabBtn.addEventListener("click", activateSuccessTab);
      failedTabBtn.addEventListener("click", activateFailedTab);
    }
  </script>
</Layout>
```

**Summary of fixes applied:**

| Issue | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| Overlay conflict (reused `sidebar-overlay`) | Changed to `drawer-overlay` everywhere — the HTML template will need a matching `<div id="drawer-overlay" class="hidden fixed inset-0 bg-black/50 z-40"></div>` added before the drawer in the HTML |
| `getElementById` without guard → implicit usage | All inner functions use `?.` or explicit `if (overlay)` guards; outer `if` blocks guard the top-level elements |
| `function` declarations → arrow functions | `openDrawer`, `closeDrawer`, `updatePagination` (tab toggles too) |
| `let` → `const` | `openBtn`, `closeBtn`, `drawer`, `rows`, `prevBtn`, `nextBtn`, `rangeStart`, `rangeEnd`, `successTabBtn`, etc. — only `currentPage` remains `let` |
| Deep nesting | Tab toggle extracted into named arrow functions (`activateSuccessTab`, `activateFailedTab`); early return used in `forEach` |
| String concatenation | `(startIdx + 1).toString()` already used; no concatenation issues |
| `querySelectorAll` early return | Used `if (idxAttr === null) return` instead of nested `if` |

